/*
 * Rocket League Mechanics Data
 * =============================
 *
 * This file contains a curated list of Rocket League mechanics, their attributes,
 * difficulty ratings, and metadata for use in the RL Mechanics web application.
 *
 * === Fields ===
 *
 * id (string, required):
 *   Unique slug kebab-case identifier for programmatic use (e.g. "half-flip").
 *
 * name (string, required):
 *   The common display name of the mechanic.
 *
 * aliases (string[], optional):
 *   Alternative names the mechanic is known by (e.g. "Cabbage Muncher" → ["Seba Flick"]).
 *
 * description (string, required):
 *   A short (1-3 sentence) explanation of what the mechanic is.
 *
 * category (string, required):
 *   The primary category the mechanic belongs to.
 *   Allowed values:
 *     "flip_reset"    — Mechanics that involve resetting your flip via ball contact
 *     "dribble_flick" — Flicks performed while the ball is carried on your car
 *     "pinch"         — Any form of ball pinch (car-to-ball, car-to-wall, etc.)
 *     "powershot"     — High-power shots on net
 *     "dribble"       — Ground or air dribbling the ball
 *     "air_dribble"   — Air dribbling specifically
 *     "redirect"      — Redirecting the ball's trajectory
 *     "pogo"          — Pogo stick-like bounces on the ball
 *     "dash"          — Dash-based movement, recovery, or speed techniques
 *     "save"          — Defensive/saving mechanics
 *     "shot"          — General shooting mechanics
 *     "movement"      — Car movement/maneuvering techniques
 *     "unknown"       — Not yet categorized
 *
 * type (string, optional):
 *   Where the mechanic is typically performed.
 *   Values: "ground", "air", "wall", "ceiling", "mixed"
 *
 * difficulty (number, required, 0-100):
 *   How difficult the mechanic is to learn and execute consistently.
 *   Calibration guide:
 *     0-20   — Bronze to Gold (basic car control)
 *     20-40  — Platinum to Diamond (intermediate)
 *     40-60  — Champion 1-3 (advanced)
 *     60-75  — Grand Champion 1-3 (high-level)
 *     75-85  — SSL / Low-Pro (elite)
 *     85-95  — Freestyler tier
 *     95-100 — Nigh impossible / undiscovered
 *   Reference points:
 *     60 ≈ Champion 3 (Ground Pinch)
 *     80 ≈ SSL average
 *     85 ≈ Pro player
 *     95 ≈ Freestyler specialist
 *
 * viability (number, required, 0-100):
 *   How effective/useful the mechanic is in a competitive match setting.
 *   0   = Never works, purely freestyle/flashy
 *   50  = Works ~50% of the time against good defenders
 *   100 = Guaranteed goal if executed
 *   Note: Even flashy mechanics can have high viability if executed in the
 *   right situation. This reflects the % chance it beats a competent defender.
 *
 * tags (string[], required):
 *   Keywords that describe the mechanic's properties. Used for filtering and
 *   search. Examples: "backwards", "recovery", "flip_cancel", "air_roll",
 *   "directional_air_roll", "musty", "stall", "multi_touch", etc.
 *
 * prerequisites (string[], optional):
 *   Array of mechanic 'id' values that are recommended to master before
 *   attempting this mechanic. Helps build a learning path.
 *
 * proponents (string[], optional):
 *   Notable players (pros or content creators) particularly known for
 *   popularizing or excelling at this mechanic.
 *
 * perform_instructions (string, optional):
 *   A brief explanation of how to perform the mechanic, including
 *   controller inputs and technique (e.g. "Air roll left + jump + boost + front flip").
 *
 * video_clips (object[], optional):
 *   Array of YouTube video references with optional time ranges for quick
 *   visual reference.
 *   Fields:
 *     url  (string, required) — Full YouTube URL
 *     start (number, optional) — Start time in seconds
 *     end   (number, optional) — End time in seconds
 *
 * === Notes ===
 * - Difficulty and viability are subjective estimates based on community
 *   consensus and may vary across patches/rankings.
 * - Categories may overlap; the 'category' field holds the primary grouping,
 *   while 'tags' capture secondary classifications.
 * - Feel free to submit corrections via PR.
 */
